s%20growth%20projection%20of%204.6%20per%20cent%20during%20the%20same%20period%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fimf-raises-india-s-economic-growth-projection-to-6-8-from-6-5-in-2024-124041600907_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fimf-raises-india-s-economic-growth-projection-to-6-8-from-6-5-in-2024-124041600907_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fimf-raises-india-s-economic-growth-projection-to-6-8-from-6-5-in-2024-124041600907_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BExpected%20To%20Remain%20Strong%26quot%3B%3A%20IMF%20Raises%20India's%20Growth%20Projection%20In%202024%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20on%20Tuesday%20raised%20India's%20growth%20projection%20to%206.8%20per%20cent%20from%20its%20January%20forecast%20of%206.5%20per%20cent%20citing%20bullish%20domestic%20demand%20conditions%20and%20a%20rising%20working-age%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%2C%20India%20continues%20to%20be%20the%20fastest-growing%20economy%20in%20the%20world%2C%20ahead%20of%20China's%20growth%20projection%20of%204.6%20per%20cent%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowth%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20remain%20strong%20at%206.8%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20and%206.5%20per%20cent%20in%202025%2C%20with%20the%20robustness%20reflecting%20continuing%20strength%20in%20domestic%20demand%20and%20a%20rising%20working-age%20population%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20latest%20edition%20of%20the%20World%20Economic%20Outlook%20released%20by%20the%20IMF%20ahead%20of%20the%20annual%20spring%20meetings%20of%20the%20IMF%20and%20the%20World%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20growth%20in%20emerging%20and%20developing%20Asia%20is%20expected%20to%20fall%20from%20an%20estimated%205.6%20per%20cent%20in%202023%20to%205.2%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20and%204.9%20per%20cent%20in%202025%2C%20a%20slight%20upward%20revision%20compared%20with%20the%20January%202024%20WEO%20Update.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIMF%20in%20its%20January%20update%20had%20projected%206.5%20per%20cent%20growth%20for%20India%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGrowth%20in%20China%20is%20projected%20to%20slow%20from%205.2%20per%20cent%20in%202023%20to%204.6%20per%20cent%20in%202024%20and%204.1%20per%20cent%20in%202025%2C%20as%20the%20positive%20effects%20of%20one-off%20factors%20--%20including%20the%20post-pandemic%20boost%20to%20consumption%20and%20fiscal%20stimulus%20--%20ease%20and%20weakness%20in%20the%20property%20sector%20persists%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20IMF%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobal%20growth%2C%20estimated%20at%203.2%20per%20cent%20in%202023%2C%20is%20projected%20to%20continue%20at%20the%20same%20pace%20in%202024%20and%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20forecast%20for%202024%20is%20revised%20up%20by%200.1%20percentage%20point%20from%20the%20January%202024%20WEO%20Update%2C%20and%20by%200.3%20percentage%20point%20from%20the%20October%202023%20WEO%2C%20the%20IMF%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolicymakers%20should%20prioritize%20steps%20toward%20greater%20economic%20resilience%20such%20as%20strengthening%20government%20finances%20and%20revitalizing%20economic%20growth%20prospects%2C%20said%20Pierre-Olivier%20Gourinchas%2C%20chief%20economist%20of%20the%20IMF.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20gloomy%20predictions%2C%20the%20global%20economy%20remains%20remarkably%20resilient%2C%20with%20steady%20growth%20and%20inflation%20slowing%20almost%20as%20quickly%20as%20it%20rose.%20The%20journey%20has%20been%20eventful%2C%20starting%20with%20supply-chain%20disruptions%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20an%20energy%20and%20food%20crisis%20triggered%20by%20Russia's%20war%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20a%20considerable%20surge%20in%20inflation%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20globally%20synchronized%20monetary%20policy%20tightening%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20economist%20said%20global%20growth%20bottomed%20out%20at%20the%20end%20of%202022%2C%20at%202.3%20per%20cent%2C%20shortly%20after%20median%20headline%20inflation%20peaked%20at%209.4%20per%20cent.%20Growth%20this%20year%20and%20next%20will%20hold%20steady%20at%203.2%20per%20cent%2C%20with%20median%20headline%20inflation%20declining%20from%202.8%20per%20cent%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%20to%202.4%20per%20cent%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025.%20Most%20indicators%20continue%20to%20point%20to%20a%20soft%20landing%2C%20he%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20also%20project%20less%20economic%20scarring%20from%20the%20crises%20of%20the%20past%20four%20years%2C%20although%20estimates%20vary%20across%20countries.%20The%20US%20economy%20has%20already%20surged%20past%20its%20pre-pandemic%20trend.%20But%20we%20now%20estimate%20that%20there%20will%20be%20more%20scarring%20for%20low-income%20developing%20countries%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20still%20struggling%20to%20turn%20the%20page%20from%20the%20pandemic%20and%20cost-of-living%20crises%2C%26quot%3B%20Gourinchas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChina's%20economy%20remains%20affected%20by%20the%20downturn%20in%20its%20property%20sector.%20Credit%20booms%20and%20busts%20never%20resolve%20themselves%20quickly%2C%20and%20this%20one%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDomestic%20demand%20will%20remain%20lackluster%20unless%20strong%20measures%20address%20the%20root%20cause.%20With%20depressed%20domestic%20demand%2C%20external%20surpluses%20could%20well%20rise.%20The%20risk%20is%20that%20this%20will%20further%20exacerbate%20trade%20tensions%20in%20an%20already%20fraught%20geopolitical%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staf